<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Campbell</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                                </placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-01-30"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 30, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your private note of the
                            23d instant, in which you state the reasons which make it necessary for
                            you to leave New Orleans for a short time, and ask permission to do so,
                            which is accordingly granted you, if you think it eminently necessary;
                            which question is left to your discretion.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis D. Campbell</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>